race.comment: DADIRRA (8) was too good here last start when leading and kicking away to score by 1.8L. She was able to negotiate the wide draw last start and Catarino will have to do so again. Only rises 1kg for that win and she won at this track and trip three starts back. Everything points to another forward showing. DOTHRAKI (10) is racing in top order, finishing behind DADIRRA last start, though he does meet that rival much better at the weights today. Sticky barrier, but if he's able to slot into the running line early on then he'll give himself the best chance. THE JESTER'S SON (5) ended his last campaign with back-to-back wins at Kalgoorlie. The 1400m journey first-up looks a good move and the claim of Tsang comes in handy. Can pick up where he left off. KALLAROO (11) is back to 1400m today which is a niggle, though he has shown glimpses in recent efforts. Include. VEVINSKY (6) won't be far away from a good draw.
